DON'T GO HERE I don't want more of a crowd. I want all the shrimp for me!!!  Ok, on all seriousness, this place is my favorite seafood place for at least 20 years. Something has changed in the flavor of the  breading in their shrimp and fish chips. Also their vegetable basket. It was bland.  On top of being bland,  they had no onion rings to accompany the basket.  It took them an additional 20 minutes to fry up another vegetable to add to my bag and they still got my order wrong. They didn't know what happened to my bag for a moment,  then they found my bag with the pick ups when I clearly was already there and had paid for my order. No apology was made, it was "have a good day". When I called  about my order being wrong,  they did not apologize and they mentioned they would have my order ready.  I asked for another day because I go out of my way to get to Frank's when I do order. She seemed bothered as if it was my fault the order was wrong. I always call my order in advance because I don't live close by and get out of work late.  My order was suppose to be ready at 8:30pm, I left out of there at 8:55pm!! They weren't super busy when I got there but as I waited for the vegetable basket they did get busy. I don't know if it's under new management but service and flavor has gone down hill and I have been going to Frank's every lent season and on other occasions for about 20 years.  Very disappointed I must say.  I guess I will try another Frank's location and hope  I get the great flavor and service I know Frank's to have.  Although this  puts me further out of my way but I will give Franks one more try.
